transcript.text: Hi welcome to on print shop.
Here we are going with Quickbook integration.
So here what is the Quickbook is an accounting software Here are some steps how it works.
Here are the benefits of Quickbook and there are two requirements.
So Quickbook should be installed on your system and you need to install one more thing which is Quickbook web connector to integrate it with our solution.
Now we will learn how we can integrate it with our solution.
So very first we are going with the admin panel.
So here in admin panel you need to go to this two configuration external service settings.
In external service settings you need to go to the accounting.
Here is Quickbook click on action edit edit Here there are two things one is online and one is desktop.
You need to select desktop.
Here there are two things are already showing one is download QWC XML file and one is password.
So when you are going to integrate it, it will not show to your system with your solution.
Then you need to select your desktop.
Then you need to select your select all and you need to select your select all.
When you set all these three things, click on save then you will get these two things.
One is download QWC XML file and one is the password.
Now just download this file and save it on your desktop.
OK now you need to go to the web connector.
So here in our solution here is the web connector.
Now you need to click on add on application.
When you click over here on add on application, it will ask you the downloaded file.
You just need to select the downloaded file and open it.
When you open the selector file, it will ask to upload it.
You just need to click on OK.
When you upload it, it will look like this.
Now there are two things available.
One is auto run like whenever you are going to sync.
So we will discuss it later.
Now we have learned we have integrated with the and you need to use the password as well over here.
When you upload it over here, you need to upload the password here and save it.
Update, select OK.
So here we have done with the integration with the solution.
Now how it works, we need to go to the admin panel.
Here is the Click to synchronize manually, just click over here.
So I'm selecting here the data so I can show you this year and I'm selecting each and everyone search.
Now you just need to tick mark over here and just click on sync.
When you click on sync it will ask to you, OK, so we have sync retreat.
Then we need to go to the again web connector.
So in web connector when you sync it.
So there are two things.
One you need to do manually after doing selecting over there, you need to click on update selected.
Or if you want to minimize this work, you can tick mark over here on auto run or you can select the timing over here like it's one minute, 2 minutes.
So it will be update selected will do after one or two minutes each and every time whenever you will sync over there.
So you don't need to come over here and each and every time you don't need to come.
You don't need to do update selected.
OK, then just hide it so it will be automatically selected.
Then you need to go to the Quickbook here you need to go to the customers customer center where you get like we have selected Ankit Gandhi.
So here you will get the invoice of Ankit Gandhi.
If you can select, you will find it over here.
So we have done with the Quickbook integration solution.
So thank you.
And if you require more information about Quickbook integration, please contact to OPS support.
Thank you.
